The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 The government on Tuesday announced traffic regulations for New Year?s Eve 

and New Year. 

Movement of goods vehicles, except those proceeding towards Posta Market from 

Howrah between 1 pm and 4 pm and towards the port area, will be restricted from 

8 am to noon on December 31 and January 1. Light commercial vehicles will be restricted 

from 8 am to noon and from 4 pm to 8 pm on both days.

Traffic regulations between 2 pm on December 31 and 2 am the following day, or 

as and when considered necessary: 

 Park Street: one-way, from west to east 

 Ho-Chi-Minh Sarani: one-way, from west to east 

 Little Russell Street: one-way, from south to north Vehicles will not be 

allowed to be parked on Park Street, between JL Nehru Road and Camac Street 

 Parking will be allowed on the following roads:

 Russell Street, parallel to the kerbs. If necessary, parking may not 

be allowed on the western side

 Western side of Mirza Ghalib Street, between Park Street and Market Street

 Rafi Ahmed Kidwai Road, between Royd Street and Shakespeare Sarani (parallel 

to the kerbs) 

Middleton Row, north-south stretch (parallel to kerb on the eastern side); and 

east-west stretch (parallel to kerb on the northern side) 

 The following roads will be made ?one way? as and when necessary:

 Royd Street, between Rafi Ahmed Kidwai Road and Mirza Ghalib Street 

 Mirza Ghalib Street, between Park Street and SN Banerjee Road

 Kyd Street, between Mirza Ghalib Street and Jawaharlal Nehru Road Middleton 

Row ? entry will be allowed from Park Street only; vehicles will not be allowed 

to enter Middleton Row from Camac Street

 Traffic may also be regulated around Indian Museum, Victoria Memorial, Birla 

Planetarium, Alipore zoo, Paraswanath temple, Kalighat temple, Thanthania Kalibari, 

New Market, Birla Mandir (Gariahat Road) and Millennium Park. 

 The Dum Dum underpass will be inaugurated on January 3, urban development minister Asok Bhattacharya said on Tuesday. It took two years for the government to construct the underpass at a cost of around Rs 10 crore. 

 he minister himself will unveil the underpass. The Gariahat market (southern conclave) will be inaugurated the next day. Over 300 hawkers who used to sell their products in the boulevard have been allotted shops in the conclave. 

 Municipal commissioner Debashis Som on Tuesday dismissed conservancy official Bikramjit Sinha for taking a bribe. He had been suspended several months ago.

 The state government will renovate some of the old cells in three central jails ? Dum Dum, Alipore and Presidency. Officials said on Tuesday the inmates had complained about poor sanitation in the cells. Jails minister Biswanath Chowdhury had held a meeting with public works department engineers at Writers? Buildings to discuss the revamp.

 Metro Railway services were disrupted for more than an hour, from 3.47 pm, on Tuesday, following an agitation by contract labourers at Tollygunge car shed. Six trains were cancelled and seven rescheduled. Normal services were resumed at 5 pm.

 Two alleged criminals, Happy Singh and Bittu Singh, were arrested on Tuesday on Rashbehari Avenue in connection with a dacoity in a Hazra Road shop. Police are now looking for a third suspect.

 A battery godown in Cossipore was razed by a fire on Monday night. Ten fire engines fought for seven hours to control the blaze.

